AC  GenProp0721
DE  2-aminoethylphosphonate (AEP) ABC transporter, type II
TP  SYSTEM
AU  Haft D
TH  0
CC  This ABC transporter is found in a number of genomes in operon-like
CC  contexts strongly suggesting a substrate specificity for
CC  2-aminoethylphosphonate (2-AEP, ciliatine). The characterized PhnSTUV
CC  system is absent in the genomes in which this system is found. These
CC  genomes encode systems for the catabolism of 2-AEP, making the need for
CC  a 2-AEP-specific transporter likely.
